<dec f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/dialogs/qfiledialog.h' l='135' type='void QFileDialog::setOption(QFileDialog::Option option, bool on = true)'/>
<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/dialogs/qfiledialog.cpp' l='717' ll='722' type='void QFileDialog::setOption(QFileDialog::Option option, bool on = true)'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/dialogs/qfiledialog.cpp' l='700'>/*!
    \since 4.5
    Sets the given \a option to be enabled if \a on is true; otherwise,
    clears the given \a option.

    Options (particularly the DontUseNativeDialogs option) should be set
    before changing dialog properties or showing the dialog.

    Setting options while the dialog is visible is not guaranteed to have
    an immediate effect on the dialog (depending on the option and on the
    platform).

    Setting options after changing other properties may cause these
    values to have no effect.

    \sa options, testOption()
*/</doc>
